---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const description = 'A clear guide to the Vaelinyan Listening Clock, a time artefact that shows one shared Vaelinya reading for every reader.';
---
<BaseLayout title="The Listening Clock" description={description}>
  <section class="page-section listening-clock-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">World · Time · Artefact</p>
    <h1>The Listening Clock</h1>
    <p class="lede">This is a fictional Vaelinya clock. It does not work like an Earth clock.</p>
    <p>Instead of showing seconds and exact minutes first, it shows four signs at once: the season, the two moons, the river pull, and the part of the day. This version uses one shared Earth reference time, UTC, so readers in different countries see the same Vaelinya reading.</p>

    <article class="clock-artefact" aria-labelledby="clock-title">
      <div class="clock-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Start here</p>
        <h2 id="clock-title">Read the four signs</h2>
        <p>Look from the outside of the clock towards the centre.</p>
        <ol class="clock-start-list">
          <li><strong>Outer ring:</strong> the seasonal arc.</li>
          <li><strong>Moon path:</strong> Aelun and Saelith.</li>
          <li><strong>River path:</strong> how strongly the moons are pulling the water.</li>
          <li><strong>Inner path:</strong> the current part of the day.</li>
        </ol>
        <div class="clock-reading" aria-live="polite">
          <p class="clock-reading-title">Current Vaelinya reading</p>
          <dl class="clock-reading-grid">
            <div class="clock-reading-row">
              <dt>Day part</dt>
              <dd id="clock-day-part">—</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="clock-reading-row">
              <dt>Month</dt>
              <dd id="clock-month">—</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="clock-reading-row">
              <dt>Arc</dt>
              <dd id="clock-arc">—</dd>
            </div>
            <div class="clock-reading-row">
              <dt>River</dt>
              <dd id="clock-river">—</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="clock-shell" aria-label="A live Vaelinyan Listening Clock showing four visible movements: the seasonal arc, the two moons, the river, and the day.">
        <div class="clock-glow" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <svg class="listening-clock" viewBox="0 0 360 360" role="img" aria-labelledby="clock-svg-title clock-svg-desc">
          <title id="clock-svg-title">The Listening Clock</title>
          <desc id="clock-svg-desc">Four circular paths show the seasonal arc, the two moons, the river pull, and the shared Vaelinya day.</desc>

          <circle class="clock-plate" cx="180" cy="180" r="164" />
          <circle class="clock-rim" cx="180" cy="180" r="158" />

          <circle class="path path-season" cx="180" cy="180" r="142" />
          <circle class="path path-moons" cx="180" cy="180" r="111" />
          <circle class="path path-water" cx="180" cy="180" r="82" />
          <circle class="path path-day" cx="180" cy="180" r="54" />

          <circle data-ring="season" class="path-progress season-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="142" pathLength="1" />
          <circle data-ring="water" class="path-progress water-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="82" pathLength="1" />
          <circle data-ring="day" class="path-progress day-progress" cx="180" cy="180" r="54" pathLength="1" />

          <circle data-dot="season" class="moving-mark season-mark" r="5" />
          <circle data-dot="aelun" class="moving-mark moon-mark aelun-mark" r="7" />
          <circle data-dot="saelith" class="moving-mark moon-mark saelith-mark" r="4.25" />
          <circle data-dot="water" class="moving-mark water-mark" r="5.5" />
          <circle data-dot="day" class="moving-mark day-mark" r="4.75" />

          <path class="water-thread" id="water-thread" d="M 106 180 Q 132 168 154 180 T 202 180 T 254 180" />

          <circle class="clock-centre" cx="180" cy="180" r="34" />
          <circle class="clock-centre-ring" cx="180" cy="180" r="25" />
          <text class="clock-centre-glyph" x="180" y="187" text-anchor="middle">✧</text>
          <text class="clock-centre-word" id="clock-centre-word" x="180" y="226" text-anchor="middle">Listening</text>
        </svg>

        <div class="clock-key" aria-label="Clock key">
          <span><i class="key-mark season-key"></i>Season</span>
          <span><i class="key-mark moon-key"></i>Moons</span>
          <span><i class="key-mark water-key"></i>River</span>
          <span><i class="key-mark day-key"></i>Day</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel read-clock-panel" aria-labelledby="read-clock-title">
      <p class="eyebrow">What the parts mean</p>
      <h2 id="read-clock-title">The clock is read from outside to inside</h2>
      <div class="reading-grid">
        <section>
          <h3>Season</h3>
          <p>The outer ring shows where the year is in the four arcs: Holding, Loosening, Opening, and Returning.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Moons</h3>
          <p>The two dots on the moon path are Aelun and Saelith. When they move closer together, their pull on the water is stronger.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>River</h3>
          <p>The river path shows the water pull. A stronger pull can mean flood rise, twin pull, or difficult crossing times.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
          <h3>Day</h3>
          <p>The inner path shows the shared Vaelinya day-part, such as first light, high day, falling light, lampkindle, or moonrise.</p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel name-guide-panel" aria-labelledby="name-guide-title">
      <p class="eyebrow">Names used by the clock</p>
      <h2 id="name-guide-title">Some names stay fixed. Some names change.</h2>
      <p class="name-guide-intro">The clock uses several groups of Vaelinya names. The moon names stay the same. The day-part, month, arc, and river names change as the shared Vaelinya reading changes.</p>

      <div class="name-guide-grid">
        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes during the day</p>
          <h3>Day-part names</h3>
          <p>These tell the reader what part of the shared Vaelinya day it is.</p>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li>Deep night</li>
            <li>First light</li>
            <li>Rising day</li>
            <li>High day</li>
            <li>Falling light</li>
            <li>Lampkindle</li>
            <li>Moonrise</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes through the year</p>
          <h3>Arc names</h3>
          <p>An arc is a large season-shape. Each arc contains three months.</p>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li>Holding</li>
            <li>Loosening</li>
            <li>Opening</li>
            <li>Returning</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card name-card-wide">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes by month</p>
          <h3>Month names</h3>
          <p>The month name shows where the shared year is inside the four arcs.</p>
          <div class="month-name-grid">
            <div><strong>Holding</strong><span>Frosthold · White Edge · Deep Quiet</span></div>
            <div><strong>Loosening</strong><span>First Run · Soft Bank · Floodwake</span></div>
            <div><strong>Opening</strong><span>Reedrise · Long Light · Thin Water</span></div>
            <div><strong>Returning</strong><span>Mistreturn · Dark Reed · Ash Frost</span></div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Changes with the moons</p>
          <h3>River names</h3>
          <p>These names describe how the water is behaving as the two moons pull at it.</p>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li>Low-water showing</li>
            <li>Moon-slack</li>
            <li>First lift</li>
            <li>Flood rise</li>
            <li>Twin pull</li>
          </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="name-card">
          <p class="name-card-label">Names that do not change</p>
          <h3>Moon names</h3>
          <p>Aelun and Saelith are the two moons. Their positions change, but their names do not.</p>
          <ol class="name-list">
            <li>Aelun — the larger visible moon</li>
            <li>Saelith — the smaller older-count moon</li>
          </ol>
        </section>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-world story-callout">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>◌</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Story note</p>
        <h2>The clock will belong to Lina too</h2>
        <p>One day Lina will find a clock that waits instead of hurrying. This page gives that artefact a clear place in the world first.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list">
      <a href="/world/time/">Back to Time</a>
      <a href="/world/time/two-moons/">The Two Moons</a>
      <a href="/world/time/calendar/">Calendar</a>
      <a href="/world/">Back to World</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const TAU = Math.PI * 2;
  const CENTRE = 180;
  const RADIUS = {
    season: 142,
    moons: 111,
    water: 82,
    day: 54,
  };

  const MONTHS = [
    ['Frosthold', 'Holding'],
    ['White Edge', 'Holding'],
    ['Deep Quiet', 'Holding'],
    ['First Run', 'Loosening'],
    ['Soft Bank', 'Loosening'],
    ['Floodwake', 'Loosening'],
    ['Reedrise', 'Opening'],
    ['Long Light', 'Opening'],
    ['Thin Water', 'Opening'],
    ['Mistreturn', 'Returning'],
    ['Dark Reed', 'Returning'],
    ['Ash Frost', 'Returning'],
  ];

  const rings = new Map(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-ring]')).map((node) => [node.dataset.ring, node]));
  const dots = new Map(Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('[data-dot]')).map((node) => [node.dataset.dot, node]));
  const centreWord = document.querySelector('#clock-centre-word');
  const waterThread = document.querySelector('#water-thread');
  const dayPartValue = document.querySelector('#clock-day-part');
  const monthValue = document.querySelector('#clock-month');
  const arcValue = document.querySelector('#clock-arc');
  const riverValue = document.querySelector('#clock-river');

  function clamp01(value) {
    return Math.max(0, Math.min(1, value));
  }

  function fractionBetween(value, start, end) {
    return clamp01((value - start) / (end - start));
  }

  function cycleFraction(now, cycleDays, offsetDays = 0) {
    const epoch = Date.UTC(2026, 0, 1);
    const elapsedDays = (now.getTime() - epoch) / 86400000;
    return ((elapsedDays + offsetDays) / cycleDays) % 1;
  }

  function titleCase(value) {
    return value.replace(/\b\w/g, (letter) => letter.toUpperCase());
  }

  function setRing(name, progress) {
    const ring = rings.get(name);
    const value = clamp01(progress);

    if (ring) {
      ring.style.strokeDashoffset = String(1 - value);
    }
  }

  function setDot(name, progress, radius) {
    const dot = dots.get(name);
    const value = clamp01(progress);

    if (dot) {
      const angle = value * TAU - Math.PI / 2;
      dot.setAttribute('cx', String(CENTRE + Math.cos(angle) * radius));
      dot.setAttribute('cy', String(CENTRE + Math.sin(angle) * radius));
    }
  }

  function getDayName(hour) {
    if (hour < 5) return 'deep night';
    if (hour < 8) return 'first light';
    if (hour < 12) return 'rising day';
    if (hour < 15) return 'high day';
    if (hour < 18) return 'falling light';
    if (hour < 21) return 'lampkindle';
    return 'moonrise';
  }

  function getWaterName(value) {
    if (value > 0.82) return 'twin pull';
    if (value > 0.62) return 'flood rise';
    if (value > 0.42) return 'first lift';
    if (value > 0.22) return 'moon-slack';
    return 'low-water showing';
  }

  function tick() {
    const now = new Date();
    const utcYear = now.getUTCFullYear();
    const utcHour = now.getUTCHours();
    const utcMinute = now.getUTCMinutes();
    const startOfYear = Date.UTC(utcYear, 0, 1);
    const startOfNextYear = Date.UTC(utcYear + 1, 0, 1);
    const season = fractionBetween(now.getTime(), startOfYear, startOfNextYear);
    const day = (utcHour + utcMinute / 60) / 24;
    const aelun = cycleFraction(now, 29.5, 2);
    const saelith = cycleFraction(now, 71, 19);
    const water = (Math.sin(aelun * TAU) + Math.sin(saelith * TAU) + 2) / 4;
    const [vaelinyaMonth, arc] = MONTHS[now.getUTCMonth()];
    const dayName = getDayName(utcHour);
    const waterName = getWaterName(water);

    setRing('season', season);
    setRing('water', water);
    setRing('day', day);
    setDot('season', season, RADIUS.season);
    setDot('aelun', aelun, RADIUS.moons);
    setDot('saelith', saelith, RADIUS.moons);
    setDot('water', water, RADIUS.water);
    setDot('day', day, RADIUS.day);

    if (waterThread) {
      const lift = Math.round(10 + water * 18);
      waterThread.setAttribute('d', `M 106 180 Q 132 ${180 - lift} 154 180 T 202 180 T 254 180`);
    }

    if (centreWord) centreWord.textContent = arc;
    if (dayPartValue) dayPartValue.textContent = titleCase(dayName);
    if (monthValue) monthValue.textContent = vaelinyaMonth;
    if (arcValue) arcValue.textContent = arc;
    if (riverValue) riverValue.textContent = titleCase(waterName);
  }

  tick();
  window.setInterval(tick, 4000);
</script>

<style>
  .listening-clock-page {
    box-sizing: border-box;
    margin-inline: auto;
    max-width: min(1180px, calc(100vw - 2rem));
    width: 100%;
  }

  .listening-clock-page > .lede,
  .listening-clock-page > p:not(.eyebrow) {
    max-width: 58rem;
  }

  .clock-artefact {
    align-items: center;
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at 78% 18%, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.32), transparent 25%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 12% 84%, rgba(83, 151, 139, 0.24), transparent 34%),
      linear-gradient(145deg, rgba(42, 29, 55, 0.98), rgba(87, 67, 91, 0.94) 58%, rgba(49, 70, 69, 0.92));
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.28);
    border-radius: 2.2rem;
    box-shadow: 0 1.4rem 3.4rem rgba(36, 28, 48, 0.22);
    color: #fff8dc;
    display: grid;
    gap: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 0.82fr) minmax(300px, 1.18fr);
    margin: 2rem 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: clamp(1.25rem, 4vw, 3rem);
    position: relative;
  }

  .clock-artefact::before {
    background:
      radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, transparent 0 36%, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.05) 36.4% 37%, transparent 37.4%),
      radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, transparent 0 55%, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.035) 55.4% 56%, transparent 56.4%);
    content: '';
    inset: 0;
    opacity: 0.85;
    pointer-events: none;
    position: absolute;
  }

  .clock-copy,
  .clock-shell {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .clock-copy .eyebrow,
  .story-callout .eyebrow {
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.82);
  }

  .clock-copy h2 {
    color: #fff8dc;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.3vw, 3.5rem);
    letter-spacing: -0.04em;
    line-height: 0.98;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .clock-copy p {
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.9);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .clock-start-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .clock-start-list li {
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.92);
    line-height: 1.45;
  }

  .clock-start-list strong {
    color: #fff8dc;
  }

  .clock-reading {
    background: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.14);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.22);
    border-radius: 1.15rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.55rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
    max-width: 24rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
  }

  .clock-reading-title {
    color: #fff8dc !important;
    font-size: 0.78rem !important;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: 0 !important;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .clock-reading-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.3rem;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .clock-reading-row {
    align-items: baseline;
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.14);
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(5.5rem, 0.72fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    padding-top: 0.35rem;
  }

  .clock-reading-row:first-child {
    border-top: 0;
    padding-top: 0;
  }

  .clock-reading-row dt,
  .clock-reading-row dd {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .clock-reading-row dt {
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.72);
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .clock-reading-row dd {
    color: #fff8dc;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 950;
    line-height: 1.2;
    text-align: right;
  }

  .clock-shell {
    align-items: center;
    aspect-ratio: 1;
    display: grid;
    justify-items: center;
    margin-inline: auto;
    max-width: 560px;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .clock-glow {
    animation: listening-glow 10s ease-in-out infinite;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.2), rgba(116, 164, 148, 0.14) 38%, transparent 70%);
    border-radius: 50%;
    filter: blur(0.28rem);
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    height: 100%;
    width: 100%;
  }

  .listening-clock {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 1rem 2rem rgba(18, 12, 24, 0.32));
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    height: auto;
    max-height: 560px;
    width: min(100%, 560px);
  }

  .clock-key {
    align-self: end;
    background: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.18);
    border-radius: 999px;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.6rem 0.9rem;
    grid-area: 1 / 1;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-bottom: 0.15rem;
    padding: 0.55rem 0.8rem;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .clock-key span {
    align-items: center;
    color: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.92);
    display: inline-flex;
    font-size: 0.86rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .key-mark {
    border-radius: 999px;
    display: inline-block;
    height: 0.65rem;
    width: 0.65rem;
  }

  .season-key { background: #e7cbff; }
  .moon-key { background: #fff8dc; }
  .water-key { background: #77d3d3; }
  .day-key { background: #ffe899; }

  .clock-plate {
    fill: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.08);
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.16);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }

  .clock-rim,
  .path,
  .path-progress {
    fill: none;
    transform: rotate(-90deg);
    transform-origin: 180px 180px;
  }

  .clock-rim {
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.36);
    stroke-width: 2.5;
  }

  .path {
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.16);
    stroke-width: 4.5;
  }

  .path-moons {
    stroke-dasharray: 2 10;
    stroke-linecap: round;
  }

  .path-water {
    stroke: rgba(119, 197, 190, 0.24);
  }

  .path-progress {
    stroke-dasharray: 1;
    stroke-dashoffset: 1;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    transition: stroke-dashoffset 900ms ease;
  }

  .season-progress {
    stroke: rgba(231, 203, 255, 0.72);
    stroke-width: 5.5;
  }

  .water-progress {
    stroke: rgba(119, 211, 211, 0.78);
    stroke-width: 5;
  }

  .day-progress {
    stroke: rgba(255, 232, 153, 0.78);
    stroke-width: 4.5;
  }

  .moving-mark {
    stroke: rgba(42, 29, 55, 0.82);
    stroke-width: 1.8;
  }

  .season-mark {
    fill: #e7cbff;
  }

  .moon-mark {
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.55rem rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.72));
    stroke-width: 2;
  }

  .aelun-mark {
    fill: #fff8dc;
  }

  .saelith-mark {
    fill: #bec8ff;
  }

  .water-mark {
    fill: #77d3d3;
    filter: drop-shadow(0 0 0.55rem rgba(119, 211, 211, 0.66));
  }

  .day-mark {
    fill: #ffe899;
  }

  .water-thread {
    fill: none;
    stroke: rgba(119, 211, 211, 0.48);
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-width: 2.5;
    transition: d 900ms ease;
  }

  .clock-centre {
    fill: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.15);
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.34);
    stroke-width: 2;
  }

  .clock-centre-ring {
    fill: rgba(42, 29, 55, 0.58);
    stroke: rgba(255, 248, 220, 0.22);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
  }

  .clock-centre-glyph,
  .clock-centre-word {
    fill: #fff8dc;
    font-family: inherit;
  }

  .clock-centre-glyph {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 800;
  }

  .clock-centre-word {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }

  .read-clock-panel,
  .name-guide-panel {
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .reading-grid,
  .name-guide-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .reading-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .name-guide-grid {
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
  }

  .reading-grid section,
  .name-card {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.68);
    border: 1px solid rgba(68, 44, 88, 0.14);
    border-radius: 1.1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
  }

  .reading-grid h3,
  .name-card h3 {
    color: #2b3137;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .reading-grid p,
  .name-card p {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .name-guide-intro {
    max-width: 58rem;
  }

  .name-card-wide {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
  }

  .name-card-label {
    color: rgba(43, 49, 55, 0.68);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 900;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    margin: 0 0 0.4rem !important;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .name-list {
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.35rem;
